<subSubSection id="CCFFFB72D5B3C734CF13C26ED58616CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6781D8E642DE73C644907F20A44D4928" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0AF33C8E164BBC99FE59ED77CA3FA160" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Native in Chongqing (Nanchuan) and Hubei (Yichang) of China. As an economically important fruit, this species has been widely cultivated in central &amp; south China, as well as in Japan, Korea, India, and some countries in Southeast Asia.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
